HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 14
By Atchley
A RESOLUTION to commend and congratulate Tim Baker,
Tennessee Fire Chiefs Association Volunteer
Fire Chief of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should honor those individuals who, during the course of
their duties, endeavor to protect the lives of their fellow citizens, braving great dangers and
putting themselves at risk to save others; and
WHEREAS, Chief Tim Baker of Waldens Creek Volunteer Fire Department is one such
individual, who was named the 2024 Volunteer Fire Chief of the Year by the Tennessee Fire
Chiefs Association in recognition of his exemplary service; and
WHEREAS, reflecting leadership both in the fire service and in the community, the
Volunteer Fire Chief of the Year award is the most prestigious honor a volunteer chief officer
can receive; it recognizes excellence and challenges chief officers to continue their professional
growth and development; and
WHEREAS, Chief Baker has been a volunteer firefighter for thirty-nine years, thirty of
which have been as chief; he followed in the footsteps of his father, who was one of the original
volunteers who helped start the Waldens Creek Volunteer Fire Department; and
WHEREAS, during his time with the department, he and his team have provided
essential services, responding to not only fires, but also wrecks, water rescues, and technical
rescues; and
WHEREAS, the need for his services and demands of the job have greatly increased
during his tenure with the Waldens Creek Volunteer Fire Department; calls per year have
increased from approximately sixty to, this year, nearly 800; and
