WHEREAS, Chief Tim Baker has done an excellent job over the years of procuring
grants and other funding for the department, money that goes toward obtaining the best
apparatuses and equipment possible and providing stipends to volunteers; and
WHEREAS, highly regarded among those in his community, Chief Baker serves as
administrator for the county's volunteer departments as well as chief of Sevier County Fire &
Rescue; and
WHEREAS, Chief Tim Baker has been outstanding in the line of duty, and his
recognition as Volunteer Fire Chief of the Year is a testament to his dedication and
professionalism in the face of danger; and
WHEREAS, Chief Baker has given selflessly in support of his department, the fire
service, and his community, and it is wholly fitting that we recognize him for his dedication to
personal excellence and his receipt of this distinguished honor; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we commend and congratulate Chief Tim Baker of Waldens Creek
Volunteer Fire Department upon being named the 2024 Volunteer Fire Chief of the Year by the
Tennessee Fire Chiefs Association, extending our sincere gratitude for his devoted service.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
